name: state_abbreviation
title: State Abbreviation
description: State abbreviation.

name: state_name
title: State Name
description: State name.

name: reporting_period
title: Reporting Period
description: Reporting period (month).

name: state_expanded_medicaid
title: State Expanded Medicaid
description: Indicates whether state has expanded Medicaid to low-income adults as of the reporting period, based on the expansion’s coverage effective date (Y=expanded Medicaid, N=has not expanded Medicaid).

name: preliminary_updated
title: Preliminary or Updated
description: Indicates whether data are from a preliminary or updated report (P=Preliminary, U=Updated).

name: final_report
title: Final Report
description: Indicates whether data are from a final report (Y=Final Report, N=Preliminary Report).

name: new_applications_submitted_to_medicaid_and_chip_agencies
title: New Applications Submitted to Medicaid and CHIP Agencies
description: The number of Medicaid and CHIP applications received by the Medicaid agency and (if applicable) the separate CHIP agency during the calendar month. Accounts transferred from the Federally-facilitated Marketplace (FFM) are excluded. This metric is calculated as the sum of Performance Indicator elements 5b and 5h.

name: new_applications_submitted_to_medicaid_and_chip_agencies_footnotes
title: New Applications Submitted to Medicaid and CHIP Agencies - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the number of Medicaid and CHIP applications received by the Medicaid agency and (if applicable) the separate CHIP agency during the calendar month. Accounts transferred from the Federally-facilitated Marketplace (FFM) are excluded.

name: applications_for_financial_assistance_submitted_to_the_state_based_marketplace
title: Applications for Financial Assistance Submitted to the State Based Marketplace
description: The total number of applications requesting financial assistance that have been received by the SBM during the calendar month, including applications received via an integrated online Marketplace/Medicaid/CHIP portal. Applications not requesting financial assistance are excluded. The metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 5n.

name: applications_for_financial_assistance_submitted_to_the_state_based_marketplace_footnotes
title: Applications for Financial Assistance Submitted to the State Based Marketplace - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the total number of applications requesting financial assistance that have been received by the SBM during the calendar month, including applications received via an integrated online Marketplace/Medicaid/CHIP portal.

name: total_applications_for_financial_assistance_submitted_at_state_level
title: Total Applications for Financial Assistance Submitted at State Level
description: The number of Medicaid and CHIP applications received by the Medicaid agency, (if applicable) the separate CHIP agency, and a State-based Marketplace (if applicable) during the calendar month. Accounts transferred from the Federally-facilitated Marketplace (FFM) are excluded. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 5a.

name: total_applications_for_financial_assistance_submitted_at_state_level_footnotes
title: Total Applications for Financial Assistance Submitted at State Level - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the number of Medicaid and CHIP applications received by the Medicaid agency, (if applicable) the separate CHIP agency, and a State-based Marketplace (if applicable) during the calendar month.

name: individuals_determined_eligible_for_medicaid_at_application
title: Individuals Determined Eligible for Medicaid at Application
description: The total number of Medicaid eligible determinations made (processed) at application by the state agency during the calendar month. This metric is calculated as the sum of Performance Indicator elements 9d and 9h when either are greater than 0; otherwise, the metric is set equal to Performance Indicator element 9a.

name: individuals_determined_eligible_for_medicaid_at_application_footnotes
title: Individuals Determined Eligible for Medicaid at Application - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the total number of Medicaid eligible determinations made (processed) at application by the state agency during the calendar month.

name: individuals_determined_eligible_for_chip_at_application
title: Individuals Determined Eligible for CHIP at Application
description: The total number of CHIP eligible determinations made (processed) at application by the state agency during the calendar month. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator element 9k when element 9k is greater than 0; otherwise, the metric is set equal to Performance Indicator element 9j.

name: individuals_determined_eligible_for_chip_at_application_footnotes
title: Individuals Determined Eligible for CHIP at Application - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the total number of CHIP eligible determinations made (processed) at application by the state agency during the calendar month.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations
description: The total number of Medicaid and CHIP eligible determinations made (processed) at application by the state agency during the calendar month. This metric is set equal to the sum of the “Individuals Determined Eligible for Medicaid at Application” and “Individuals Determined Eligible for CHIP at Application” metrics in this dataset.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the total number of Medicaid and CHIP eligible determinations made (processed) at application by the state agency during the calendar month.

name: medicaid_and_chip_child_enrollment
title: Medicaid and CHIP Child Enrollment
description: A point-in-time count of the number of children enrolled in Medicaid and the number of individuals enrolled in CHIP as of the last day of each month. Note that since some states use CHIP to extend coverage to adults, this measure is not strictly limited to children in all states. Includes only those individuals who are eligible for comprehensive benefits. This metric is calculated as the sum of Performance Indicator elements 8c, 8f, and 8h when 8c and 8f are greater than 0; otherwise, the metric is set equal to 0.

name: medicaid_and_chip_child_enrollment_footnotes
title: Medicaid and CHIP Child Enrollment - footnotes
description: Footnotes for a point-in-time count of the number of children enrolled in Medicaid and the number of individuals enrolled in CHIP (including separate CHIP and Medicaid-expansion CHIP) as of the last day of each month.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_enrollment
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Enrollment
description: A point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in Medicaid or CHIP as of the last day of each month. Includes only those individuals who are eligible for comprehensive benefits. This metric is calculated as the sum of Performance Indicator elements 8a and 8h.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_enrollment_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Enrollment - footnotes
description: Footnotes for a point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in Medicaid or CHIP as of the last day of each month.

name: total_medicaid_enrollment
title: Total Medicaid Enrollment
description: A point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in Medicaid as of the last day of each month. Includes only those individuals who are eligible for comprehensive benefits. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 8a.

name: total_medicaid_enrollment_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid Enrollment - footnotes
description: Footnotes for a point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in Medicaid as of the last day of each month.

name: total_chip_enrollment
title: Total CHIP Enrollment
description: A point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in CHIP (including separate CHIP and Medicaid-expansion CHIP) as of the last day of each month. Note that since some states use CHIP to extend coverage to adults, this measure is not strictly limited to children in all states. Includes only those individuals who are eligible for comprehensive benefits. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 8h.

name: total_chip_enrollment_footnotes
title: Total CHIP Enrollment - footnotes
description: Footnotes for a point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in CHIP (including separate CHIP and Medicaid expansion CHIP) as of the last day of each month.

name: total_medicaid_adult_enrollment
title: Total Adult Medicaid Enrollment
description: A point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in adult MAGI and non-MAGI Medicaid as of the last day of each month. Includes only those individuals who are eligible for comprehensive benefits. This metric is calculated as the sum of Performance Indicator elements 8d and 8g.

name: total_medicaid_adult_enrollment_footnotes
title: Total Adult Medicaid Enrollment - footnotes
description: Footnotes for a point-in-time count of the number of individuals enrolled in adult MAGI and non-MAGI Medicaid as of the last day of each month.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_in_less_than_24_hours
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed in Less than 24 Hours
description: The number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred less than 24 hours after the date the application was received by the agency. Determinations made using non-MAGI rules, applications that have not yet received a final determination, and determinations at annual renewal are not included in this metric. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 12f.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_in_less_than_24_hours_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed in Less than 24 Hours - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred less than 24 hours after the date the application was received by the agency.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_between_24_hours_and_7_days
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed Between 24 Hours and 7 Days
description: The number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred between 24 hours and 7 days after the date the application was received by the agency. Determinations made using non-MAGI rules, applications that have not yet received a final determination, and determinations at annual renewal are not included in this metric. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 12g.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_between_24_hours_and_7_days_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed Between 24 Hours and 7 Days - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred between 24 hours and 7 days after the date the application was received by the agency.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_between_8_days_and_30_days
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed Between 8 Days and 30 Days
description: The number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred between 8 days and 30 days after the date the application was received by the agency. Determinations made using non-MAGI rules, applications that have not yet received a final determination, and determinations at annual renewal are not included in this metric. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 12h.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_between_8_days_and_30_days_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed Between 8 Days and 30 Days - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred between 8 days and 30 days after the date the application was received by the agency.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_between_31_days_and_45_days
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed Between 31 Days and 45 Days
description: The number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred between 31 days and 45 days after the date the application was received by the agency. Determinations made using non-MAGI rules, applications that have not yet received a final determination, and determinations at annual renewal are not included in this metric. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 12i.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_between_31_days_and_45_days_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed Between 31 Days and 45 Days - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred between 31 days and 45 days after the date the application was received by the agency.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_in_more_than_45_days
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed in More than 45 Days
description: The number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred more than 45 days after the date the application was received by the agency. Determinations made using non-MAGI rules, applications that have not yet received a final determination, and determinations at annual renewal are not included in this metric. This metric is set equal to Performance Indicator data element 12j.

name: total_medicaid_and_chip_determinations_processed_in_more_than_45_days_footnotes
title: Total Medicaid and CHIP Determinations Processed in More than 45 Days - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the number of final determinations on applications made by the Medicaid and CHIP agency using MAGI rules that occurred more than 45 days after the date the application was received by the agency.

name: total_call_center_volume
title: Total Call Center Volume (Number of Calls)
description: The total number of calls received by each call center or hotline that serves Medicaid and CHIP applicants or enrollees in the state. Call centers reported in this metric may serve additional state human services programs such as SNAP, but the metric excludes calls received by call centers that primarily serve an SBM. The metric is set equal to the value states report in Performance Indicator data element 1.

name: total_call_center_volume_footnotes
title: Total Call Center Volume (Number of Calls) - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the total number of calls received by each call center or hotline that serves Medicaid and CHIP applicants or enrollees in the state.

name: average_call_center_wait_time
title: Average Call Center Wait Time (Minutes)
description: The average wait time in whole minutes for calls received by all call centers reported in the metric above. Wait times between 0 and 29 seconds are rounded down to the nearest whole minute, including 0 zero minutes. The metric is set equal to the value states report in Performance Indicator data element 2.

name: average_call_center_wait_time_footnotes
title: Average Call Center Wait Time (Minutes) - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the average wait time in whole minutes for calls received by all call centers reported in the metric above. Wait times between 0 and 29 seconds are rounded down to the nearest whole minute, including 0 zero minutes.

name: average_call_center_abandonment_rate
title: Average Call Center Abandonment Rate
description: The average abandonment rate for all call centers reported in the call center volume metric above. The abandonment rate is calculated as the number of calls abandoned by the caller (numerator) divided by the total call volume (denominator). The metric is set equal to the value states report in Performance Indicator data element 3.

name: average_call_center_abandonment_rate_footnotes
title: Average Call Center Abandonment Rate - footnotes
description: Footnotes for the average abandonment rate for all call centers reported in the call center volume metric above.
